                                                                                                               Kingfisher salary alert
          OUR BUREAU                              
	Mumbai, July 29: Kingfisher Airlines has warned its 6,000 employees that their salaries could be delayed.        
	The warning was given in an email sent out by executive vice-president Hitesh Patel.        
	Along with all other airlines, we are in a tight situation regarding finances. You can expect to be in embarrassing situations with our vendors; your salaries may be delayed but never beyond the 7th, the email said.        
	Kingfisher suffered a net loss of Rs 243 crore in the April-June quarter, a 53.8 per cent increase over the Rs 158-crore loss a year ago. Revenues fell 6 per cent to Rs 1,314 crore from Rs 1,398 crore.        
	For the full year ended March 31, Kingfishers net loss stood at Rs 1,609 crore on an income of Rs 5,270 crore.                                                                                                                                                           
